Sciclone buys stock from resigning chairman . SciClone Pharmaceuticals Inc said Friday it bought 1 . 88 million shares of its common stock for $ 5 . 95 million from its resigning chairman Thomas Moore . Sciclone said its board elected Jere Goyan , a former U . S . Food and Drug Administration commissioner and currently president and chief operating officer of Alteon Inc , to replace Moore , who resigned effective immediately . The company said it has the right to repurchase shares from Moore at a fixed discount rate . 
